com.esri.mo2.map.lbl
Interface LabelEngine

All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseLabelEngine
public interface LabelEngine

Determines the optimal placement of Labels that are handed to it by TextSymbols. This process is implemented in two phases. Before the first phase begins, the LabelEngine initializes itself via the clear method. During the first phase, one or more TextSymbols will pass label details to the LabelEngine through the add method. During the second phase, the LabelEngine will be asked to produce the resulting optimal placements, via the process() method - during this phase, the LabelEngine will call-back each TextSymbol that originated a label, and request it to draw the label with the optimized location and orientation.

LE_NO_WEIGHT

public static final int LE_NO_WEIGHT
When used with the TextSymbol.setFeatureWeight method, this identifier indicates that a feature has no special importance compared with its label, so that the label can be placed over the top of the feature. The opposite is true when used with TextSymbol.setLabelWeight()

See Also:

LE_ONE_LABEL_PER_NAME

public static final int LE_ONE_LABEL_PER_NAME
Indicates that when labeling multiple features, only one label will be displayed for all features having the same label string. For example, a collection of line features representing the same highway would be labeled with a single label showing the highway name.

See Also:

LE_ONE_LABEL_PER_SHAPE

public static final int LE_ONE_LABEL_PER_SHAPE

Method Detail

init

public void init(Labeling callback,
                 Envelope extent,
                 Transform transform)
Initiates the first phase of label processing. After calling this method, all previous labels are no longer considered, and only "new" labels added by the add method will be considered.

The map extent and world coordinates-to-pixel transformation are supplied at this point.

Parameters:
callback - the object that will be notified by LabelEngine to draw the results
extent - the map extent
transform - the transformation from world coordinates to pixels

add

public void add(Dimension box,
                FeatureGeometry featureGeometry,
                TextSymbol textSymbol,
                String text)
Adds a label to the LabelEngine with the given dimension and text.

Parameters:
box - the dimensions of the label
featureGeometry - the feature geometry
textSymbol - the text symbol
text - the label name

addProtectedBox

public void addProtectedBox(Envelope box)
Adds the given protected box.

Parameters:
box - the protected box

process

public void process()
Initiates the second phase of label processing. After calling this method, the LabelEngine will callback the Labeling object that was specified in a previous call to the init method.
